      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/16/9",
      "text": [
        " : \"لاَ يُضَمَّنُ اَلصَّائِغُ وَ لاَ اَلْقَصَّارُ وَ لاَ اَلْحَائِكُ إِلاَّ أَنْ يَكُونُوا مُتَّهَمِينَ فَيَجِيئُونَ بِالْبَيِّنَةِ فَيُخَوَّفُ وَ يُسْتَحْلَفُ لَعَلَّهُ يُسْتَخْرَجُ مِنْهُ شَيْءٌ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3928 - Ibn Muskan narrated from Abu Basir, from Abu Abdillah (as), who said:\n\"The goldsmith, the launderer, and the weaver are not held liable unless they are suspected. In such cases, they must bring evidence, and they should be made to swear an oath and be warned, perhaps something may be revealed from them.\""
        ]
      }
    },
